              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-T"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The Tritium-Ti target, 10 mm diameter, and 5.2",
                "mg/cm2 thickness. The deuteron beam energy was 3 MeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The uranium metal (about 2 g) disks with 16 mm diameter",
                "were sealed in a pure Al foil of 0.2 mm thickness. It",
                "was sandwiched between two standardized thinner uranium",
                "samples. The standardized thin samples were made of the",
                "same uranium as the thick ones. The abundance of",
                "Uranium isotopes:",
                "                  U-235, 90.2%",
                "                  U-234, 1.1%",
                "                  U-236, 0.3 %",
                "                  U-238, 8.4%"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Gamma-spectrometers."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "FISCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The sample was mounted in a double fission",
                "chamber, covered with Cd of 1 mm thick in order to",
                "shield it from the thermal neutrons from the",
                "environment."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Four samples were irradiated for 30 h at a",
                "distance of about 5 cm from the neutron source in the",
                "direction of zero degree."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Fission product activities were measured by",
                "HPGe gamma-ray spectrometry. The gamma ray spectra",
                "were collected over a period varying from 30 seconds",
                "up to two months, and the gamma ray spectra were",
                "analyzed by the decay program SPAN. The fission",
                "yields were obtained by FYAUTOLS."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MONITOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Absolute measurement of fission rate"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Corrections were made for coincidence losses, pileup",
                "losses in the counting system, influence of the",
                "background neutrons, self absorption of gamma ray,",
                "independent yields and influence from other uranium",
                "isotopes."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The sum of the yields directly measured was 61.1% for",
                "the light mass groups, and 53.2% for the heavy mass",
                "groups."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "HISTORY": [
